org.unc.lac.baboon.subscription

Class AbstractActionControllerSubscription

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.unc.lac.baboon.subscription.AbstractActionControllerSubscription
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractTaskControllerSubscription, HappeningControllerSubscription

    public abstract class AbstractActionControllerSubscription
extends java.lang.Object
    This class defines an AbstractActionControllerSubscription as a list of ActionController objects, which are subscribed to a topic. It is used internally by framework and should not be known by user.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Ariel Ivan Rabinovich, Juan Jose Arce Giacobbe

      • AbstractActionControllerSubscription

        public AbstractActionControllerSubscription(Topic topic)
                                     throws NotSubscribableException
        Constructor.
        Parameters:
        topic - The topic to which ActionController objects will be subscribed
        Throws:
        NotSubscribableException -
        • When the topic is null
        • If there are guard callbacks on the topic and Topic.setGuardCallback and Topic.permission sizes are different.

    • Method Detail

      • addAction

        protected boolean addAction(ActionController actionController)
                     throws NotSubscribableException
        This method appends the given actionController to the end of actionsList
        Parameters:
        actionController - ActionController object to be appended to actionsList. The permission and guard callback corresponding to this ActionController are determined by the order (or index).
        Returns:
        true if actionsList changed as a result of the call
        Throws:
        NotSubscribableException -
        • If the ActionController object does not have a GuardProvider annotated method to handle a guard declared in the topic
        See Also:
        Topic.permission, Topic.setGuardCallback
